As a Project Manager I want to see the Epic Due Date in JIRA Portfolio so that I can quickly see how project deadlines (fixed) may be impacted by the iterative development work within a given release.

Business Context: We work on the development with Scrum, but many projects are traditionally (waterfall) determined and we do our best to meet those deadlines.  As a result, it would be extremely useful to simply add the Epic Due Date to JIRA Portfolio so that we could combine those very different worlds in one place.  It would also help a lot of our PMs get off MS Project and actually use JIRA Portfolio!

