As a Project Manager I want to be able to secure _some_ plans from recalculation so they can be used for historical reference as a baseline. I would like the ability to turn this "lock" on and off. 

Unfortunately there is no security with JIRA Portfolio which would prevent someone from clicking the Recalculate button when in Manual mode; the only options are Automatically (where Portfolio updates after each change you make) or Manually with the button.

Because I am referencing multiple plans throughout the day, some of which are for the purpose mentioned above, and some of which are "working plans" I update weekly it is easy to accidentally recalculate the wrong plan.

